The paint would look much better and be easier to use, if you used raw canvas, pre Gesso.   Store bought canvas's use a white paint 'Gesso' to cover the canvas, as a base ... so that color paints will not soak through, (as some colors might soak through faster or easier, limiting their effectiveness in the painted subject matter.  Using raw canvas, would drip less, and soak into the canvas better.  I have used water diluted paint on raw canvas for a few paintings in the past with successful results.
